Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.21,0:00:40.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But was that really true, what you said before?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.61,0:01:45.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's definitely what he said.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.70,0:01:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe he's mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.91,0:01:49.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.12,0:01:53.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.05,0:02:07.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suwa, about those three suspects assigned to Yoshioka,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.09,0:02:10.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,it's particularly likely one's an accomplice.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.76,0:02:11.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.31,0:02:20.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hmm? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.99,0:02:28.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is there something on my face?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.12,0:02:32.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then what the heck is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.87,0:02:38.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. Ha-ha. No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.33,0:02:42.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I keep seeing people whispering in secret. Is something going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.92,0:02:44.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.05,0:02:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it's nothing. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.84,0:02:51.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. N-Nothing at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.27,0:02:58.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha, it's nothing. There's nothing going on. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.23,0:03:00.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ha-ha-ha, nothing to worry about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.32,0:03:06.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,R-Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.54,0:03:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've finished examining the suspect in the Haido City case.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.08,0:03:24.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.50,0:03:26.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, regarding that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.22,0:03:29.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, I've outdone myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.68,0:03:35.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I'm amazing, don't you agree?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.14,0:03:41.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, really. I really need to brag about my examination.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.98,0:03:49.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's like the feeling after you've eaten some\Nkatsudon while watching a drama that just came out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.24,0:03:55.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,TAKAGI!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.33,0:03:56.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.87,0:03:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Don't give us "What is it?"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:03.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C'mon, we want you to tell us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.92,0:04:05.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's right, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.71,0:04:11.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, there are others here who's hearts are ready, Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.34,0:04:16.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hearts ready? Hearts ready for what?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.47,0:04:18.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-T-Takagi!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.06,0:04:22.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now, now. So, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.60,0:04:23.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.15,0:04:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's... yours, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.86,0:04:30.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something about Inspector Megure's phone call?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.70,0:04:34.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, that's very funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.49,0:04:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm talking about Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.00,0:04:40.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:43.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See it shining there on Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s finger?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.04,0:04:48.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.01,0:04:51.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That ring. The ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.72,0:04:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.93,0:04:56.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.31,0:05:00.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.60,0:05:02.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.90,0:05:06.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A ring?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.52,0:05:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've never seen that ring before. And what's\Nmore, it's on the ring finger of her left hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.95,0:05:14.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who could have given her that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.87,0:05:18.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, no. Calm down. Remain calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.33,0:05:20.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Keep your cool. Keep your cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.20,0:05:23.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Go and ask Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.33,0:05:27.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}. About that ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.01,0:05:33.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. I found someone I like.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.18,0:05:35.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwako{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.94,0:05:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.59,0:05:38.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Miwa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.31,0:05:42.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh-hah-hah. Just like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.77,0:05:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it's on the ring finger of the left hand that means...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.90,0:05:46.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An engagement.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.19,0:05:49.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what it means, right?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.77,0:05:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What it means is what I want to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.82,0:05:56.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? That ring? It isn't yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.45,0:05:57.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-No.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.95,0:06:00.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Didn't buy it; never seen it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.04,0:06:03.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then, who the heck did?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.79,0:06:08.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.26,0:06:22.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be a patrolman?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.81,0:06:23.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe it's a judge.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.31,0:06:25.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I heard it was a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.77,0:06:28.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, hold on for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.23,0:06:30.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.52,0:06:34.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Quiet down!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.03,0:06:36.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I must be missing something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.99,0:06:37.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.24,0:06:40.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, sorry. And then?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.79,0:06:44.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Someone is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.21,0:06:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Somebody's dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.30,0:06:57.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I understand, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. I'll be there soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.01,0:07:01.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, let's go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.97,0:07:04.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's trouble at a villa in Okutama.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.85,0:07:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.73,0:07:06.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.19,0:07:09.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, please take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.94,0:07:11.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No problem. Now about what we were discussing...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.71,0:07:15.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.32,0:07:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right here there's...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.58,0:07:28.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Big trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.49,0:07:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's one step to a glorious future.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.35,0:07:36.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Having your heart ready is OK, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.55,0:07:40.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the light flashes off the ring on Detective Satou's\Nleft hand, will Detective Takagi make a decision at last?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.14,0:07:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.64,0:07:44.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With the body of a child and the brain of an adult.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.39,0:07:46.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.03,0:09:48.69,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Wow, what a magnificent ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.89,0:09:52.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That sure is an amazing number of gemstones.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.48,0:09:54.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are they all diamonds?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.98,0:09:58.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This the first time I've ever seen anything like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.32,0:10:00.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.82,0:10:03.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a ring I had made to commemorate the debut of my 100th work.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.61,0:10:07.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I had "100th" engraved on the reverse side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.78,0:10:08.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.11,0:10:13.77,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The truth is I had ordered 100 diamonds to be affixed, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.49,0:10:17.67,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Moroguchi Masataka (52)\NMystery Author
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.05,0:10:19.15,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If I did that, the size of the ring would be too large, and I was against that.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.63,0:10:24.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess that's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.39,0:10:31.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, excuse me. I need to change the tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.60,0:10:37.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't it unusual to be using a cassette tape recorder nowadays?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.12,0:10:41.04,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's generally all digital recording now, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.69,0:10:43.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Dejima Kakuji (34)\NWriter
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.42,0:10:45.76,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I'm just not happy unless I can see the tape spinning.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.36,0:10:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And I'm scared of errors with digital.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.62,0:10:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.33,0:10:55.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In truth, I'm the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.96,0:11:00.60,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All of my fellow cameraman are using digital cameras, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.04,0:11:02.38,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Tarumi Wataru (33)\NCameraman
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.85,0:11:06.31,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,I've been using this analog guy for so long I just can't let it go.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.09,0:11:12.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well if I can't finish this up soon, I'll be in trouble...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.06,0:11:19.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, I'm sorry to interrupt the pile of analog stories, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.73,0:11:24.44,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Anabuki Harue (33)\NMagazine Editor
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.14,0:11:24.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The deadline for Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}'s on-going serialization is getting close.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.24,0:11:29.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you're done with the useless chatter, can you finish what you came to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.36,0:11:31.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't be so grumpy, Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.91,0:11:36.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The official conversation between me and\NDetective Mouri isn't until tomorrow morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.25,0:11:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This evening we'll feast on my home cooking, and after\Na good rest, we'll do it in the morning sunlight tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.51,0:11:48.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right, Writer{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.55,0:11:51.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. This is, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.76,0:11:55.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something like an introductory rehearsal meeting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.39,0:12:02.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's even on the announcement page in this\Nmonth's edition. Look, the author Moroguchi Masataka...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.73,0:12:09.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Speaks with great detective Mouri Kogorou on\Nthe new dawn of mysteries. There's a lot of publicity.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.74,0:12:11.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.41,0:12:13.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Let me see...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.79,0:12:20.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}? What's with that face?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.38,0:12:25.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm just thinking he's kind of different from what I imagined.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.71,0:12:28.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Different? You mean Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.05,0:12:30.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.76,0:12:36.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the sensei's mysteries pay excessive attention to minute details.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.68,0:12:41.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I thought for sure he would be an easily irritable and highly strung person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.15,0:12:46.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.53,0:12:48.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.73,0:12:50.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have a ruler?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.70,0:12:54.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yes. I do happen to have a measuring tape.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.45,0:13:00.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.71,0:13:07.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When compared to the other authors, the\Ncharacters of my name are one millimeter smaller!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.38,0:13:09.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you trying to make a fool of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.55,0:13:15.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,N-Not at all. It was just the way the size of the characters came out properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.64,0:13:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that's the case then make characters of the other author's names smaller!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.48,0:13:22.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is a piece of crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.61,0:13:27.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.02,0:13:29.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It won't happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.99,0:13:32.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course not!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.61,0:13:33.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.03,0:13:36.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that area he's pretty high strung.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.16,0:13:42.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Really! My chief editor before you, Akiba{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, was really good.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.25,0:13:45.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He would grant me anything I desired.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.21,0:13:50.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah! He sounds like an excellent editor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.55,0:13:57.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When searching for a file photo or when\Ninvestigating or collecting specialized knowledge regarding a trick,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.64,0:14:01.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,he would exhaust his flesh and bones without sparing for my sake.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.31,0:14:07.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Until even his very life was exhausted...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.65,0:14:13.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-He passed away?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.11,0:14:19.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. In the spring of this year his body was found in his home.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.62,0:14:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With all the locks locked, in the middle of a sealed room.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.87,0:14:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A-A sealed room? Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.71,0:14:33.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It had to be, right? It wasn't one of my mysteries after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.34,0:14:38.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The truth is I thought I would write a book based on his death, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.26,0:14:41.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was stopped by Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.02,0:14:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course! His sudden death was well-known in the publication industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.19,0:14:50.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If a novel like that were published,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.86,0:14:55.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I figured it would lead to a bunch of gossip articles on the Internet.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.36,0:14:56.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.86,0:15:00.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gossip is just gossip. It's not the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.41,0:15:04.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides if it was called a memorial of sorts to my editor Akiba,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.58,0:15:07.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,don't you think, on the contrary, it would be a hit?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.79,0:15:09.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Well, I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.34,0:15:14.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.63,0:15:18.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Crap, I'm out of lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.39,0:15:22.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why don't you use mine?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.65,0:15:40.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd like to say this is something I use a lot, a pencil. Even though it's analog.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.87,0:15:44.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll use it proudly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.12,0:15:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, for now, since tomorrow's plans have been decided,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.96,0:15:55.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and the production will be tomorrow morning,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.92,0:15:58.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd better wrap these up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.10,0:16:07.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I don't waste the film.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.03,0:16:21.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, we continued the program\Nplanning for two more hours, only breaking for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.45,0:16:25.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we had only known all that work would be useless...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.99,0:16:31.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, because, the single main participant in those plans was...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.34,0:16:34.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.13,0:16:37.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's already five o'clock in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.47,0:16:39.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.84,0:16:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sensei?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.47,0:16:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.01,0:16:45.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.01,0:16:47.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is he still sleeping?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.22,0:16:52.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah, it's possible he was up late last night working.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.27,0:16:55.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then let's use the master key and wake him up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.94,0:17:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing is, the sensei really hates it\Nwhen other people come into his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.95,0:17:05.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So there isn't a master key. It seems he stole it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.62,0:17:08.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.21,0:17:18.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have a bad feeling. A sensation like a\Nstrangling in my chest, suffocating me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.05,0:17:22.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like it always does at a time like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.26,0:17:29.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'd say the time of death was about an hour ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.35,0:17:34.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,An almond odor. Cyanide poisoning?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.85,0:17:37.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a coffee stain around his mouth.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.02,0:17:40.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did he drink it with the coffee?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.91,0:17:46.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All of the locks in the room are secure.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.78,0:17:54.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only way in was what I used when I came in, a\Nventilation window that only a child could get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.17,0:18:01.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And probably what's in his hand is the key to this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.26,0:18:02.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:06.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, this is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.85,0:18:08.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.81,0:18:18.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased is the mystery author, Moroguchi Masataka{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, 52 years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.82,0:18:22.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cause of death is suffocation from the ingestion of cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.65,0:18:26.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And from the coffee stains around his mouth, most likely...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.70,0:18:33.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He either mixed the cyanide in his coffee and\Ndrank it or was forced to drink it, but which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.17,0:18:38.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't say he was forced to drink it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.42,0:18:45.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door and windows in this room\Nsecurely locked, so it was definitely a sealed room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.18,0:18:50.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not to mention Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s holding the key\Nto this room in his hand, and there are no spare keys.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.89,0:18:53.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it must be suicide, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.73,0:19:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,H-How come? Someone could have\Nplaced cyanide on his coffee cup beforehand,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.44,0:19:03.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so a crime in this sealed room is still possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.90,0:19:09.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course they would have to know that\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drinks coffee when he wakes up in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.78,0:19:15.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot! People don't normally drink coffee while holding keys, do they?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.83,0:19:22.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, of course, it would be completely unreasonable to\Ngrab it right after realizing that the coffee had been poisoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.63,0:19:29.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he was probably holding that key before\Ndrinking the poison as some kind of message.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.89,0:19:36.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, but Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was scheduled to have an\Ninterview with you this morning, wasn't he, Mouri{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.40,0:19:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So maybe because he overslept he grabbed the key in haste and\Njust before leaving the room he drank the coffee to wake himself up?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.57,0:19:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on! Look more carefully.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.28,0:19:54.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The coffee cup is lying right next to the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.33,0:19:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.79,0:20:00.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the coffee maker is in the kitchen over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.21,0:20:06.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If he was in a rush, he would have drank\Nthe coffee in the kitchen where he got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.76,0:20:11.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He wouldn't have bothered to place it on a\Nsaucer and bring it over to the bed to drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.55,0:20:14.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, did you think about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.56,0:20:20.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Someone came to wake up Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} this\Nmorning, poured him a cup of coffee and mixed in the cyanide,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.35,0:20:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,and brought it over to his bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.40,0:20:27.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asking him to be quick, they handed him the key and left the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.44,0:20:28.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can't be it either.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:36.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that was the case, then whoever it was would have had\Nto leave the room before Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} drank the coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.54,0:20:40.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to get Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to lock the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.21,0:20:44.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's up to the person whether they drink the coffee right away or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.25,0:20:49.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But since he was being pressured he probably drank it right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.34,0:20:55.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But maybe Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} has a sensitive tongue\Nand couldn't drink it right away because it was too hot.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.51,0:20:56.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.31,0:21:01.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} absolutely loved coffee.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.39,0:21:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hot or lukewarm, he always said it was good.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.78,0:21:08.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.23,0:21:09.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.82,0:21:11.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a well known fact in the editorial department.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.41,0:21:15.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And you guys are?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.16,0:21:21.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. I'm the editor in charge of Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r}, Anabuki.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.67,0:21:25.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for the two behind me, on the right is the cameraman, Tarumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.38,0:21:27.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the left is the writer, Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.30,0:21:35.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So the three of you came here this morning\Nto Moroguchi's villa for the planned interview?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.39,0:21:39.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, all three of us spent the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.52,0:21:43.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would sure be rough to come here by five in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.85,0:21:46.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, it's strange, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.73,0:21:52.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since this room was sealed, you would have had to\Nbreak down the door or smash a window to get inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.82,0:21:55.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there's no sign of that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.53,0:21:57.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, how did you get in?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.95,0:21:59.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As for that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.70,0:22:01.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This brat did it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.33,0:22:10.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r} came in through the ventilation\Nwindow and unlocked the door from the inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.59,0:22:15.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,so we could get into the room also.\NAnd then we found Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.72,0:22:19.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that window was open?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.35,0:22:21.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.22,0:22:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like it's only wide enough for a child to squeeze through.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.06,0:22:31.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Still, if this was a suicide, then how come\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was holding the key when he died?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.28,0:22:39.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well it could be that he didn't want any\Nof us in the villa to be suspected of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.16,0:22:43.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And like I said a second ago if this was a murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.91,0:22:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then unless the murderer said, "Close the door\Nand drink the coffee while holding the key" to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.79,0:22:51.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would be impossible to create this situation.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.42,0:22:55.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, any idea why Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would commit suicide?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.34,0:22:57.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, not really.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.76,0:23:00.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He didn't seem that type at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.68,0:23:03.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.98,0:23:08.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, he could have had troubles that he didn't discuss with certain people.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.65,0:23:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It seems his previous chief editor, Akiba,\Ncommitted suicide in the spring of this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.74,0:23:19.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he might have felt responsible for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.79,0:23:26.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well anyway, let's wait for forensics to arrive.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.00,0:23:31.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If this was murder, then the culprit's\Nfingerprints should have been left around here somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.96,0:23:36.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because if the culprit had poured the coffee or\Nopened and closed the door while wearing gloves,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.13,0:23:39.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} would have become suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.43,0:23:42.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And there was no chance to wipe them off after the room is locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.52,0:23:48.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course, that's only if you guys didn't touch anything before we arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.65,0:23:54.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We didn't Detective Mouri warned us not to go in until the police arrived.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.69,0:23:58.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've already decided it was suicide. There's no reason to call forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.20,0:24:00.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.83,0:24:04.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Doesn't it bother you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.00,0:24:06.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.71,0:24:08.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The R-l-N-G.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.62,0:24:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.88,0:24:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I'd be lying if I said it didn't bother me,\Nbut we're in the middle of an investigation...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.72,0:24:21.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's not what I meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.14,0:24:26.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where are you looking? It's over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.02,0:24:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This man's ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.23,0:24:32.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The word "100th" is upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.11,0:24:39.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, you're right. But maybe he just put in on wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.36,0:24:45.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But this man was really neurotic, I don't think he'd make a mistake like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.99,0:24:47.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Also this ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.79,0:24:53.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? It has so many diamonds on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.55,0:24:59.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That's it! This really was a murder after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.97,0:25:04.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The motive for the murder was this ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.64,0:25:14.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After killing Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the culprit switched the real ring with\Na fake ring; but, in a rush, ended up putting it on the opposite way.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.73,0:25:17.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} never take off his ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.94,0:25:28.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, that's right. He was really fond of it. He\Nalways kept it on even while taking a bath or when in bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.75,0:25:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it's like Detective Takagi says, then the\Npossibility of this being a murder has gotten stronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.83,0:25:37.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One more puzzle has arisen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.09,0:25:44.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. The culprit could have have only\Nswitched the rings after Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.68,0:25:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Therefore, the culprit must have still been in the room at that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:48.64,0:25:54.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So then how did the culprit escape from this locked room?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.90,0:25:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How did they get the key into Mogoguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.23,0:26:05.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Or maybe after poisoning Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the\Nkiller took the key and left the room, locking the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.74,0:26:10.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then they somehow managed to find a way to\Nreturn the key to Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand from the outside.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.66,0:26:15.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only thing that was open was that ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.96,0:26:19.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's about four meters from there to the corpse's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:21.92,0:26:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,With that much distance...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.84,0:26:26.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Is something like that even possible?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.64,0:26:37.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, while we wait for forensics to show up, let's hear from you guys.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.15,0:26:43.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where were you and what were you\Ndoing before Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s body was found?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.24,0:26:46.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First up is Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.20,0:26:50.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I-I was fixing this tape recorder in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.20,0:26:58.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It wasn't working very well. The tape inside got\Nmessed up and when I tried to rewind it, it made this sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.59,0:27:03.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-That sure is a strange sound.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.01,0:27:05.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Next is Tarumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.09,0:27:12.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After I finished setting up my photography stuff, I was\Nalso in my room organizing the negatives for some other work.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.35,0:27:15.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Using these rubber bands to tie them up.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.35,0:27:19.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. Then, next is Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.23,0:27:24.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I was in my room as well checking the galleys for other authors.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.74,0:27:30.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That reminds me, Auntie. You had a metal tape\Nmeasure, didn't you? Do you always carry that?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.41,0:27:37.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Because the sensei always asks me\Nto measure things, like the size of words.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.75,0:27:41.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But if it's just to measure words then why not a ruler?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.38,0:27:48.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know, boy. It's not just used for\Nwords, you can measure lots of stuff with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.68,0:27:52.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like a door or a window that can be used for a trick.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.47,0:27:54.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know a lot about him.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.98,0:27:58.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We learned a lot from Akiba before he died.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.65,0:28:01.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since he and the three of us joined the company the same year.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.07,0:28:05.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Although I ended up quitting and became a freelance writer.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:06.11,0:28:08.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see. So that's it?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.49,0:28:12.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Uhm, Detective Satou.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.87,0:28:15.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This isn't related to the case, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.29,0:28:16.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What is it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.08,0:28:20.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's probably forensics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.13,0:28:23.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sorry, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}. Later, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.13,0:28:28.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.39,0:28:33.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? It's real?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.72,0:28:36.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The ring is genuine?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.43,0:28:37.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.56,0:28:42.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we took it to the station right away and had\Nan expert take a look at it, so we're positive it's real.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.98,0:28:46.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then I guess the culprit's motive wasn't the ring after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:46.86,0:28:48.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It seems so.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.11,0:28:54.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why? What reason did the culprit have for taking the ring off?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.08,0:28:59.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, come to think of it, when we took the ring off we found a strange mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.83,0:29:01.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A strange mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:01.29,0:29:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes. Right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.21,0:29:09.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It faded a lot, but there's a blackened circle around this finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:09.76,0:29:11.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.72,0:29:15.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Blood? Why is there blood there?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.76,0:29:21.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps he cut himself while shaving and he touched the cut.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.69,0:29:22.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.69,0:29:28.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See? There's a cut under his right jaw. There's no mistaking it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.57,0:29:33.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Incidentally, on the coffee cup, this saucer,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.49,0:29:39.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the coffee maker or on the doorknob there\Nwere no prints other than those of the corpse.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.70,0:29:41.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.42,0:29:46.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,U-Uhm, Detective Takagi.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.13,0:29:47.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.71,0:29:52.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This may be inappropriate at a time like this, but I really wanted to say...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:53.93,0:29:55.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-What is it, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.14,0:29:58.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Congratulations on your engagement!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.64,0:30:02.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.94,0:30:10.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because, look! The ring that Detective Satou has on he\Nleft hand ring finger, that's an engagement ring, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.11,0:30:14.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Looks like it...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.28,0:30:19.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Looks like it?" Are you saying you didn't give it to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.83,0:30:22.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope. It's someone else's.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.75,0:30:26.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she's replaced you with a more reliable and good looking guy?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.50,0:30:27.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.09,0:30:29.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.59,0:30:33.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You suppose so? Shouldn't you find out for sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.55,0:30:40.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It'll be nice if I could, but I'm kind of scared of the answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.60,0:30:43.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Seriously. It's like having to walk a tightrope.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.52,0:30:49.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you haven't fallen off the rope already?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.27,0:30:50.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.52,0:30:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, Dad, stop teasing him!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.52,0:30:53.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it! So that's why!
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.95,0:30:57.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why the culprit took the ring off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.57,0:31:01.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was to make sure the "tightrope\Nwalk" in the sealed room would be a success.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.79,0:31:05.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I still don't quite get this.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.63,0:31:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The door and the windows in the room were locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.00,0:31:15.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The deceased, Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, died\Nfrom drinking coffee poisoned with cyanide.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.13,0:31:20.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his left hand was the one and only key to the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.10,0:31:25.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only opening was a ventilation\Nwindow that a child could barely get through.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.98,0:31:36.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just from this it looks like he killed himself and didn't\Nwant anybody else in the villa to be suspected of murder.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.74,0:31:44.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The problem is that the ring on the middle finger of his left\Nhand that was holding the key, was placed on upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.58,0:31:50.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,According to this woman, Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} almost never took his ring off.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.04,0:31:55.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And since he's not the type who would put it on wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.92,0:32:01.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then after someone poisoned\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, for some reason they took the ring off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.51,0:32:05.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when putting it back on they accidentally put it on upside down.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.60,0:32:11.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe they took the ring off because there was blood on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.94,0:32:17.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I mean, there was blood under the ring\Nfrom when he cut himself shaving, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.70,0:32:22.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then maybe the culprit took the ring off his finger to wipe the blood off.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.33,0:32:27.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, if that was the case, then they\Nwould have wiped the blood off his finger too.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.58,0:32:32.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even if they wiped the blood off the ring, it'd be\Nmeaningless if there was still blood on the finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.00,0:32:36.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe the culprit wiped the blood without taking the ring off?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:36.59,0:32:37.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I suppose so.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.09,0:32:40.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe that guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.39,0:32:43.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was sewing?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.01,0:32:47.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,S-Sewing? What do you mean, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.06,0:32:55.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, I mean... Remember? Earlier when you were making me the\Ndust cloth I take to school, you were wearing a ring, right, Ran{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-neechan{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.03,0:32:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Eh? Oh, you mean the thimble?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.45,0:33:04.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When you have that on it's easier to\Npass the thread through the needle, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.99,0:33:11.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's wrong! Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, a thimble is used in order to push on the needle.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.25,0:33:18.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, really? I thought for sure that they used that\Nring to push something through the hole in the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.76,0:33:24.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh well, I was just wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.44,0:33:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Put something through the hole in the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.36,0:33:40.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why the ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.45,0:33:49.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.08,0:33:50.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Uncle...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.83,0:33:52.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rubber bands!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.75,0:33:54.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Rubber bands?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.34,0:34:02.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First you chain the rubber bands together, then you pass the\Nbands through the ring and create something like a slingshot.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.26,0:34:10.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You hook the top and bottom of the key on both ends of the rubber\Nbands and you fling it into the room through the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.89,0:34:14.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You can control the length of the rubber bands by how many you attach.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.81,0:34:22.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And of course this was done after poisoning\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} and leaving the room with the door locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.99,0:34:29.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the only person who could have done this is the\Nperson who is still wearing tons of rubber bands on his wrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.58,0:34:33.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cameraman, Tarumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}! It was you!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.87,0:34:37.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.34,0:34:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. It wasn't me.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.84,0:34:41.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wrong again, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.17,0:34:48.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, if that was the case, shouldn't the rubber bands still be in the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.93,0:34:51.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you're flinging them into the room along with the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.85,0:34:53.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-Then he only used one side.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.81,0:34:59.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He held one end of the rubber bands\Nand hung the key on the other end to fling it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.36,0:35:03.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way he just has to pull on the end\Nhe was holding to be able to get it back.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.15,0:35:06.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But even if he was able to get them back that way,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.49,0:35:14.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,the knots in the rubber bands would get caught in the\Nring and pull, making the corpse's arm dangle from the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.87,0:35:21.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Besides, would the culprit really choose an impossible task\Nlike flinging a key into the palm of a hand with rubber bands?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.05,0:35:28.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it failed, people would think the key was\Njust thrown in through the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.51,0:35:30.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, that might happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.18,0:35:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It will happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.89,0:35:38.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, I could put him to sleep and\Nperform the deduction show like always, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.06,0:35:41.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Detective Satou is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.19,0:35:44.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came close to finding out once already.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.53,0:35:49.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Guess I'll have to just lead them into realizing the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.16,0:35:55.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're right, Uncle. I don't think even the\Npeople at the circus can do a trick like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.62,0:36:00.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The circus? Are you talking about magicians?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.00,0:36:06.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Detective Takagi was saying that he\Nwas walking a tightrope with Detective Satou.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.84,0:36:12.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the two of them are doing a circus trick, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.85,0:36:15.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aah, w-wait, Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}! That was...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.73,0:36:17.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What did you mean, Takagi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.79,0:36:20.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Conan{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}, what was mean!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.00,0:36:23.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wait, walking a\Ntightrope. Walking a tightrope.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.19,0:36:26.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, there is one thing!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.74,0:36:31.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Something long and narrow that won't get\Ncaught in the ring and you can get back right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.53,0:36:34.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, you finally figured it out, Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.08,0:36:40.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The thing that Anabuki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, the editor, carries...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.75,0:36:42.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The metal tape measure.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.25,0:36:44.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.26,0:36:48.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So she put the measuring tape through the ring?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.59,0:36:51.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, she just hooked the tip of the measuring tape on the ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.22,0:36:59.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then she put the measuring tape through the hole in the key and\Nsent it from outside the ventilation window into Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.77,0:37:01.56,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like a tightrope walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.56,0:37:06.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a sec. When did she put the\Nmeasuring tape through the hole in the key?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.11,0:37:11.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did it immediately after poisoning Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.41,0:37:17.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key went on the measuring tape first, then she hooked the tip\Nonto the ring, and then stretched it out to the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.08,0:37:21.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if the body of the tape measure along\Nwith the key is hooked on the window edge,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.25,0:37:31.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,then, afterwards, she just has to lift it up from the window and the\Nkey will follow the measuring tape right into Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.05,0:37:34.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And, of course, you can get it back with just one button.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.39,0:37:45.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What I meant was, how do you lock the door if the key\Nwas already on the tape measure before you left the room?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.48,0:37:47.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.73,0:37:53.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe she stretched out the measuring tape after\Ncommitting the crime and leaving the room with the door locked.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.57,0:37:57.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe she did it after going outside to the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.54,0:38:01.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Y-You know, since it's a rigid metal\Ntape measure, you could use it like a stick.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.83,0:38:05.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And if you cleverly get the tip of the tape\Nmeasure to the corpse on the bed and hook it on the ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.25,0:38:08.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That can only be done up to one meter.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.46,0:38:14.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anything longer than that and it'll bend before\Neven reaching either the palm of the hand or the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.10,0:38:20.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And besides, what's the point of taking the\Nring off if you just need to hook something on it?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.39,0:38:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,T-True.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.73,0:38:26.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. If only there was something long and thin like a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:27.15,0:38:31.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But none of the three suspects had anything like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.90,0:38:37.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We checked around the villa and there's\Nbeen no report of anything like that being found.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.74,0:38:39.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How could there be?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.08,0:38:46.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Unlike a rubber band, it would have to be something that wouldn't\Nget caught in the ring and was thin, smooth and long like a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.63,0:38:51.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus you'd have to always be able to wrap it up like a\Ntape measure. There can't be anything that convenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.30,0:38:53.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,W-Wait a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.26,0:38:55.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Could that be a...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.43,0:38:56.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ca-
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.26,0:38:57.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cassette Tape!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.97,0:39:05.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now I see, using a cassette tape you can\Npull out the tape and put it through the ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.31,0:39:10.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And pull the end of the tape back to where the\Ncassette is placed outside the ventilation window.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.28,0:39:15.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way after you poison Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r},\Nyou lock the door and leave the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.66,0:39:20.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then from outside the ventilation window you put\Nthe tape you left there through the hole in the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.62,0:39:23.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And just by lifting the tape up high...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.12,0:39:29.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The key will slide down the tape due to\Ngravity and arrive on the corpse's hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.88,0:39:39.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After that, if you wind up the tape, it'll slip through the key and the\Nring and return to the cassette. And so the sealed room is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.60,0:39:45.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means the only person who was able to use this trick\Nis the person who habitually carries a cassette tape around.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.98,0:39:51.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And who wouldn't regarded as\Nsuspicious by the police when examined later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.86,0:39:53.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That person is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.19,0:39:56.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The writer, Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.70,0:39:58.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It couldn't be anyone except you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.95,0:40:06.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Most likely you said you had some last minute checks for the\Narrangements of the interview that was planned this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.08,0:40:10.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you asked Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} to let you into his room.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.29,0:40:16.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then when he wasn't looking you\Nmixed cyanide in his coffee, thus killing him.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.88,0:40:20.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then you used the trick we just discussed making this a sealed room.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.80,0:40:22.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? Are we wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.52,0:40:31.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we'll know if we just examine the cassette tape you're carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.61,0:40:38.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You want to say that the tape will be\Ntwisted, but I told you about that, didn't I?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.95,0:40:40.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That this recorder...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.32,0:40:43.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't working correctly.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.66,0:40:46.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I have plenty of tapes that are twisted.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.87,0:40:52.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Plus it makes a loud noise whenever it winds\Nsomething up, someone would have heard that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:55.51,0:41:05.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If I didn't use this and just quickly reeled in the tape by hand\Nthen a large portion would have been twisted. Go ahead and check.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:05.39,0:41:08.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have a tape like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:09.56,0:41:10.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nope.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.02,0:41:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The pencil!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.11,0:41:18.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You stuck the pencil you borrowed from\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} last night into the hole in the cassette to wind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.28,0:41:26.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This way you can wind the tape back in a short amount of\Ntime without using the recorder and without damaging it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:27.00,0:41:30.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I did it a lot when I was a kid too.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.33,0:41:38.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whenever I was goofing around and ended up pulling out a lot of\Ntape I had to wind up, I'd put it on my knee and roll it up with a pencil.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.34,0:41:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And when Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was talking about examining the\Ntape, it wasn't about whether the tape was twisted or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:46.01,0:41:52.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Like we said before, there was blood under the ring on his left middle finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.52,0:41:55.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For some reason there was one place where it was rubbed off.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.86,0:41:59.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it should be somewhere on the cassette tape that you're carrying.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.32,0:42:06.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The one you used for the sealed room\Ntightrope walk, a tape with Moroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s blood on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.41,0:42:07.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,D-Dejima{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.16,0:42:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! Could it be, because of Akiba?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.17,0:42:16.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hah, a tightrope walk? Akiba used to say that a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.21,0:42:21.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That his relationship with\NMoroguchi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-sensei{\r} was a continuous tightrope walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.34,0:42:24.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A tightrope walk?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.10,0:42:28.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akiba was a careful sort-of guy,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.39,0:42:33.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but ever since he became in charge of the\Nsensei, he was always wearing a bandage somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.69,0:42:35.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why do you think that was?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.06,0:42:39.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As the sensei told him to, he was testing them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.48,0:42:45.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All the murder tricks the sensei thought up, he was\Nusing his own body to confirm if they would work or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.20,0:42:50.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Of course taking meticulous care to make sure he didn't die for real.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.83,0:42:56.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey! So the incident where Akiba was found dead in a sealed room was...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:56.54,0:43:01.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah. When I was sorting through the\Neffects in Akiba's desk at the office, I found it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.51,0:43:08.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A notebook of tricks in which was\Nwritten the exact same way that Akiba died!
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.51,0:43:11.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then why didn't you turn that over to the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.06,0:43:19.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It would've been useless. If put on the spot, the\Nsensei would have just said, "Akiba did that on his own."
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.65,0:43:21.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it was still an accident, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.19,0:43:26.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, the sensei said it like this in another interview:
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.82,0:43:32.04,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At this age, I've finally started to understand the murderer's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.33,0:43:36.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As a mystery writer, there's nothing more joyous than that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.50,0:43:40.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's what he said. And that's when I knew for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:41.21,0:43:44.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What the sensei wanted to know by making use of Akiba...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.05,0:43:46.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Wasn't the reality of the tricks...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.55,0:43:51.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But rather the mentality of the murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:18.60,0:45:21.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So? I've been wondering about it for a while now.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.73,0:45:23.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,About what?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.40,0:45:28.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't "about what" me. What did you\Nmean about walking on a tightrope with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.65,0:45:31.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no. That was, well...
Dialogue: 0,0:45:32.03,0:45:36.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was your ring! Detective Satou, you always say you dislike shiny things.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:36.58,0:45:39.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So Detective Takagi was wondering why you're wearing a ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.87,0:45:44.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I guess it's good that she's just as blunt as Uncle.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.34,0:45:49.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this? You mean this charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.30,0:45:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,C-Charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.09,0:45:53.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's all?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:53.72,0:45:55.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.89,0:45:57.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Silver and turquoise.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.18,0:46:05.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you wear one on your left hand ring finger it'll keep the\Nbad bugs away, killing two birds with one stone, Yumi said.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.52,0:46:07.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So I'm doing it too.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.49,0:46:12.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You know I'm cursed and I hate bugs, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.53,0:46:16.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, no, when Yumi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said bugs she didn't mean those bugs.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.41,0:46:21.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,l-In that case, Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, please wear my ring!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.92,0:46:23.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On your left hand ring finger!
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.04,0:46:28.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,OK, that's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.42,0:46:36.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Man, I bet she was grilled by everybody today.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:36.93,0:46:40.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all Satou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} is wearing my ring...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:40.31,0:46:43.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On her left hand ring finger.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.48,0:46:47.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But today I need to act dignified.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:47.94,0:46:49.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And face them like a man.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.74,0:46:57.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Takagi, we heard about it. Satou's ring.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.20,0:46:58.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here it comes...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.54,0:46:59.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.62,0:47:02.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, it was just a charm!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.08,0:47:05.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What's going on with everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.00,0:47:07.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's a good thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.75,0:47:08.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't let it bother you.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.17,0:47:13.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But to think that she doesn't know the meaning of the left hand ring finger...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.09,0:47:16.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That makes it even more exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.64,0:47:20.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, I didn't tell her yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.68,0:47:24.23,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The meaning of that ring. Oh well...
